obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE FOREIGN EXCHANGE MANAGEMENT ACT, 1999`
  line _________
  line `ARRANGEMENT OF SECTIONS`
  line __________
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `1. Short title, extent, application and commencement.`
  line `2. Definitions.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `R EGULATION AND MANAGEMENT OF FOREIGN EXCHANGE`
  line `3. Dealing in foreign exchange, etc.`
  line `4. Holding of foreign exchange, etc.`
  line `5. Current account transactions.`
  line `6. Capital account transactions.`
  line `7. Export of goods and services.`
  line `8. Realisation and repatriation of foreign exchange.`
  line `9. Exemption from realisation and repatriation in certain cases.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `A UTHORISED PERSON`
  line `10. Authorised person.`
  line `11. Reserve Bank’s powers to issue directions to authorised person.`
  line `12. Power of Reserve Bank to inspect authorised person.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `C ONTRAVENTION AND PENALTIES`
  line `13. Penalties.`
  line `14. Enforcement of the orders of Adjudicating Authority.`
  line `14A. Power of recover arrears of penalty.`
  line `15. Power to compound contravention.`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `A DJUDICATION AND APPEAL`
  line `16. Appointment of Adjudicating Authority.`
  line `17. Appeal to Special Director (Appeals).`
  line `18. Appellate Tribunal.`
  line `19. Appeal to Appellate Tribunal.`
  line `20. [ Omitted.]`
  line `21. Qualifications, for appointment of Special Director (Appeals).`
  line `22. [ Omitted.]`
  line `23. Terms and Conditions of service Special Director (Appeals).`
  line `24. [ Omitted. ]`
