  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `25. [ Omitted.]`
  line `26. [ Omitted.]`
  line `27. Staff of Special Director (Appeals).`
  line `28. Procedure and powers of Appellate Tribunal and Special Director (Appeals).`
  line `29. [ Omitted.]`
  line `30. [ Omitted.]`
  line `31. [ Omitted.]`
  line `32. Right of appellant to take assistance of legal practitioner or chartered accountant and of`
  line `Government, to appoint presenting officers.`
  line `33. Officers and employees etc., to be public servant.`
  line `34. Civil court not to have jurisdiction.`
  line `35. Appeal to High Court.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `D IRECTORATE OF E NFORCEMENT`
  line `36. Directorate of Enforcement.`
  line `37. Power of search, seizure, etc.`
  line `37A. Special provisions relating to assets held outside India in contravention of section 4.`
  line `38. Empowering other officers.`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `39. Presumption as to documents in certain cases.`
  line `40. Suspension of operation of this Act.`
  line `41. Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  line `42. Contravention by companies.`
  line `43. Death or insolvency in certain cases.`
  line `44. Bar of legal proceedings.`
  line `44A. Powers of Reserve Bank not to apply to International Financial Services Centre.`
  line `45. Removal of difficulties.`
  line `46. Power to make rules.`
  line `47. Power to make regulations.`
  line `48. Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  line `49. Repeal and saving.`
