obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `THE FOREIGN EXCHANGE MANAGEMENT ACT, 1999`
  line `A CT N O. 42 OF 1999`
  line `[29 th December, 1999.]`
  line `An Act to consolidate and amend the law relating to foreign exchange with the objective of`
  line `facilitating external trade and payments and for promoting the orderly development and`
  line `maintenance of foreign exchange market in India.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Fiftieth Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title, extent, application and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Foreign`
  line `Exchange Management Act, 1999.`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall also apply to all branches, offices and agencies outside India owned or controlled by a`
  line `person resident in India and also to any contravention thereunder committed outside India by any person`
  line `to whom this Act applies.`
  line `( 4 ) It shall come into force on such date 1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference in`
  line `any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming into`
  line `force of that provision.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ Adjudicating Authority ” means an officer authorised under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16;`
  line `2 [( b ) “ Appellate Tribunal ” means the Appellate Tribunal referred to in section 18;]`
  line `( c ) “ authorised person ” means an authorised dealer, money changer, off-shore banking unit or`
  line `any other person for the time being authorised under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 10 to deal in foreign`
  line `exchange or foreign securities;`
  line `3 [( cc ) “Authorised Officer” means an officer of the Directorate of Enforcement authorised by the`
  line `Central Government under section 37A;]`
  line `( d ) “ Bench ” means a Bench of the Appellate Tribunal;`
  line `( e ) “ capital account transaction ” means a transaction which alters the assets or liabilities, including`
  line `contingent liabilities, outside India of persons resident in India or assets or liabilities in India of`
  line `persons resident outside India, and includes transactions referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) of section 6;`
  line `( f ) “ Chairperson ” means the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal;`
  line `( g ) “ chartered accountant ” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949);`
  line `3 [( gg ) “Competent Authority” means the Authority appointed by the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 37A;]`
  line `( h ) “ currency ” includes all currency notes, postal notes, postal orders, money orders, cheques,`
  line `drafts, travellers cheques, letters of credit, bills of exchange and promissory notes, credit cards or such`
  line `other similar instruments, as may be notified by the Reserve Bank;`
  line `1. 1st June, 2000, vide notification No. G.S.R. 371(E), dated 1st May, 2000, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3( i ).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 165, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 138 (w.e.f. 9-9-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-4
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Page 4`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `( i ) “ currency notes ” means and includes cash in the form of coins and bank notes;`
  line `( j ) “ current account transaction ” means a transaction other than a capital account transaction and`
  line `without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing such transaction includes, —`
  line `( i ) payments due in connection with foreign trade, other current business, services, and`
  line `short-term banking and credit facilities in the ordinary course of business,`
  line `( ii ) payments due as interest on loans and as net income from investments,`
  line `( iii ) remittances for living expenses of parents, spouse and children residing abroad, and`
  line `( iv ) expenses in connection with foreign travel, education and medical care of parents, spouse`
  line `and children;`
  line `( k ) “ Director of Enforcement ” means the Director of Enforcement appointed under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 36;`
  line `( l ) “ export ”, with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means —`
  line `( i ) the taking out of India to a place outside India any goods,`
  line `( ii ) provision of services from India to any person outside India;`
  line `( m ) “ foreign currency ” means any currency other than Indian currency;`
  line `( n ) “ foreign exchange ” means foreign currency and includes, —`
  line `( i ) deposits, credits and balances payable in any foreign currency,`
  line `( ii ) drafts, travellers cheques, letters of credit or bills of exchange, expressed or drawn in Indian`
  line `currency but payable in any foreign currency,`
  line `( iii ) drafts, travellers cheques, letters of credit or bills of exchange drawn by banks, institutions`
  line `or persons outside India, but payable in Indian currency;`
  line `( o ) “ foreign security ” means any security, in the form of shares, stocks, bonds, debentures or any`
  line `other instrument denominated or expressed in foreign currency and includes securities expressed in`
  line `foreign currency, but where redemption or any form of return such as interest or dividends is payable in`
  line `Indian currency;`
  line `( p ) “ import ”, with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means bringing into India`
  line `any goods or services;`
  line `( q ) “ Indian currency ” means currency which is expressed or drawn in Indian rupees but does not`
  line `include special bank notes and special one rupee notes issued under section 28A of the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line `( r ) “ legal practitioner ” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961);`
  line `( s ) “ Member ” means a Member of the Appellate Tribunal and includes the Chairperson thereof;`
  line `( t ) “ notify ” means to notify in the Official Gazette and the expression “ notification ” shall be`
  line `construed accordingly;`
  line `( u ) “ person ” includes —`
  line `( i ) an individual,`
  line `( ii ) a Hindu undivided family,`
  line `( iii ) a company,`
  line `( iv ) a firm,`
  line `( v ) an association of persons or a body of individuals, whether incorporated or not,`
  line `( vi ) every artificial juridical person, not falling within any of the preceding sub-clauses, and`
  line `( vii ) any agency, office or branch owned or controlled by such person;`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Page 5`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `( v ) “ person resident in India ” means —`
  line `( i ) a person residing in India for more than one hundred and eighty-two days during the`
  line `course of the preceding financial year but does not include —`
  line `( A ) a person who has gone out of India or who stays outside India, in either case —`
  line `( a ) for or on taking up employment outside India, or`
  line `( b ) for carrying on outside India a business or vocation outside India, or`
  line `( c ) for any other purpose, in such circumstances as would indicate his intention to`
  line `stay outside India for an uncertain period;`
  line `( B ) a person who has come to or stays in India, in either case, otherwise than —`
  line `( a ) for or on taking up employment in India, or`
  line `( b ) for carrying on in India a business or vocation in India, or`
  line `( c ) for any other purpose, in such circumstances as would indicate his intention to`
  line `stay in India for an uncertain period;`
  line `( ii ) any person or body corporate registered or incorporated in India,`
  line `( iii ) an office, branch or agency in India owned or controlled by a person resident outside`
  line India,
  line `( iv ) an office, branch or agency outside India owned or controlled by a person resident in`
  line India;
  line `( w ) “ person resident outside India ” means a person who is not resident in India;`
  line `( x ) “ prescribed ” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line `( y ) “ repatriate to India ” means bringing into India the realised foreign exchange and —`
  line `( i ) the selling of such foreign exchange to an authorised person in India in exchange for`
  line `rupees, or`
  line `( ii ) the holding of realised amount in an account with an authorised person in India to the`
  line `extent notified by the Reserve Bank,`
  line `and includes use of the realised amount for discharge of a debt or liability denominated in foreign`
  line `exchange and the expression “ repatriation ” shall be construed accordingly;`
  line `( z ) “ Reserve Bank ” means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3`
  line `of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line `( za ) “ security ” means shares, stocks, bonds and debentures, Government securities as defined in the`
  line `Public Debt Act, 1944 (18 of 1944), savings certificates to which the Government Savings Certificates`
  line `Act, 1959 (46 of 1959) applies, deposit receipts in respect of deposits of securities and units of the Unit`
  line `Trust of India established under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Unit Trust of India Act, 1963`
  line `(52 of 1963)* or of any mutual fund and includes certificates of title to securities, but does not include`
  line `bills of exchange or promissory notes other than Government promissory notes or any other instruments`
  line `which may be notified by the Reserve Bank as security for the purposes of this Act;`
  line `( zb ) “ service ” means service of any description which is made available to potential users and`
  line `includes the provision of facilities in connection with banking, financing, insurance, medical assistance,`
  line `legal assistance, chit fund, real estate, transport, processing, supply of electrical or other energy,`
  line `boarding or lodging or both, entertainment, amusement or the purveying of news or other information,`
  line `but does not include the rendering of any service free of charge or under a contract of personal service;`
  line `( zc ) “ Special Director (Appeals) ” means an officer appointed under 1 [section 17];`
  line `( zd ) “ specify ” means to specify by regulations made under this Act and the expression “ specified ”`
  line `shall be construed accordingly;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s.165, for “section 18” (w.e.f. 26 -5-2017).`
  line `*Now see the Unit Trust of India (transfer of Undertaking of Repeal) Act, 2002 (58 of 2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `( ze ) “ transfer ” includes sale, purchase, exchange, mortgage, pledge, gift, loan or any other form of`
  line `transfer of right, title, possession or lien.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `R EGULATION AND MANAGEMENT OF FOREIGN EXCHANGE`
  line `3. Dealing in foreign exchange, etc. — Save as otherwise provided in this Act, rules or regulations`
  line `made thereunder, or with the general or special permission of the Reserve Bank, no person shall —`
  line `( a ) deal in or transfer any foreign exchange or foreign security to any person not being an`
  line `authorised person;`
  line `( b ) make any payment to or for the credit of any person resident outside India in any manner;`
  line `( c ) receive otherwise through an authorised person, any payment by order or on behalf of any`
  line `person resident outside India in any manner.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purpose of this clause, where any person in, or resident in, India receives`
  line `any payment by order or on behalf of any person resident outside India through any other person`
  line `(including an authorised person) without a corresponding inward remittance from any place outside`
  line `India, then, such person shall be deemed to have received such payment otherwise than through an`
  line `authorised person;`
  line `( d ) enter into any financial transaction in India as consideration for or in association with`
  line `acquisition or creation or transfer of a right to acquire, any asset outside India by any person.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purpose of this clause, “ financial transaction ” means making any payment`
  line `to, or for the credit of any person, or receiving any payment for, by order or on behalf of any person,`
  line `or drawing, issuing or negotiating any bill of exchange or promissory note, or transferring any`
  line `security or acknowledging any debt.`
  line `4. Holding of foreign exchange, etc. — Save as otherwise provided in this Act, no person resident in`
  line `India shall acquire, hold, own, possess or transfer any foreign exchange, foreign security or any`
  line `immovable property situated outside India.`
  line `5. Current account transactions. — Any person may sell or draw foreign exchange to or from an`
  line `authorised person if such sale or drawal is a current account transaction:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, in public interest and in consultation with the Reserve`
  line `Bank, impose such reasonable restrictions for current account transactions as may be prescribed.`
  line `6. Capital account transactions. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), any person may`
  line `sell or draw foreign exchange to or from an authorised person for a capital account transaction.`
  line `( 2 ) The Reserve Bank may, in consultation with the Central Government, specify —`
  line `1 [( a ) any class or classes of capital account transactions, involving debt instruments, which are`
  line permissible;]
  line `( b ) the limit up to which foreign exchange shall be admissible for such transactions:`
  line `2 [( c ) any conditions which may be placed on such transactions;]`
  line `3 [ Provided that the Reserve Bank or the Central Government shall not impose any restrictions on`
  line `the drawal of foreign exchange for payment due on account of amortisation of loans or for`
  line `depreciation of direct investments in the ordinary course of business.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 139, for Clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 15-10-2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 139, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-10-2019).`
  line `3. The Proviso subs. by s. 139, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-7
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Page 7`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `1 [ ( 2A ) The Central Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, prescribe —`
  line `( a ) any class or classes of capital account transactions, not involving debt instruments, which are`
  line permissible;
  line `( b ) the limit up to which foreign exchange shall be admissible for such transactions; and`
  line `( c ) any conditions which may be placed on such transactions. ]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( 4 ) A person resident in India may hold, own, transfer or invest in foreign currency, foreign security`
  line `or any immovable property situated outside India if such currency, security or property was acquired, held`
  line `or owned by such person when he was resident out side India or inherited from a person who was resident`
  line `outside India.`
  line `( 5 ) A person resident outside India may hold, own, transfer or invest in Indian currency, security or`
  line `any immovable property situated in India if such currency, security or property was acquired, held or`
  line `owned by such person when he was resident in India or inherited from a person who was resident in`
  line India.
  line `( 6 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of this section, the Reserve Bank may, by regulation, prohibit,`
  line `restrict, or regulate establishment in India of a branch, office or other place of business by a person`
  line `resident outside India, for carrying on any activity relating to such branch, office or other place of`
  line business.
  line `3 [( 7 ) For the purposes of this section, the term “ debt instruments ” shall mean, such instruments as`
  line `may be determined by the Central Government in consultation with the Reserve Bank.]`
  line `7. Export of goods and services. — ( 1 ) Every exporter of goods shall —`
  line `( a ) furnish to the Reserve Bank or to such other authority a declaration in such form and in such`
  line `manner as may be specified, containing true and correct material particulars, including the amount`
  line `representing the full export value or, if the full export value of the goods is not ascertainable at the`
  line `time of export, the value which the exporter, having regard to the prevailing market conditions,`
  line `expects to receive on the sale of the goods in a market outside India;`
  line `( b ) furnish to the Reserve Bank such other information as may be required by the Reserve Bank`
  line `for the purpose of ensuring the realisation of the export proceeds by such exporter.`
  line `( 2 ) The Reserve Bank may, for the purpose of ensuring that the full export value of the goods or such`
  line `reduced value of the goods as the Reserve Bank determines, having regard to the prevailing market`
  line `conditions, is received without any delay, direct any exporter to comply with such requirements as it`
  line `deems fit.`
  line `( 3 ) Every exporter of services shall furnish to the Reserve Bank or to such other authorities a`
  line `declaration in such form and in such manner as may be specified, containing the true and correct material`
  line `particulars in relation to payment for such services.`
  line `8. Realisation and repatriation of foreign exchange. — Save as otherwise provided in this Act,`
  line `where any amount of foreign exchange is due or has accrued to any person resident in India, such person`
  line `shall take all reasonable steps to realise and repatriate to India such foreign exchange within such period`
  line `and in such manner as may be specified by the Reserve Bank.`
  line `9. Exemption from realisation and repatriation in certain cases. — The provisions of sections 4`
  line `and 8 shall not apply to the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) possession of foreign currency or foreign coins by any person up to such limit as the Reserve`
  line `Bank may specify;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 139 (w.e.f. 15-10-2019).`
  line `2. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by s. 139, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-10-2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 139, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
