obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line 21
  line `( c ) every appeal from any decision or order of the Appellate Board under sub-section ( 3 ) or`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) of section 52 of the repealed Act shall, if not filed before the commencement of this`
  line `Act, be filled before the High Court within a period of sixty days of such commencement:`
  line `Provided that the High Court may entertain such appeal after the expiry of the said period of sixty`
  line `days if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal within`
  line `the said period.`
  line `( 6 ) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section ( 3 ), the mention of particular matters in`
  line `sub-sections ( 2 ), ( 4 ) and ( 5 ) shall not be held to prejudice or affect the general application of section 6 of`
  line `the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with regard to the effect of repeal.`
